cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "FounderBench: Evaluating LLM Agents on Sequential Startup Decisions"
message: "If you use FounderBench, please cite this software and the associated paper."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Wang
    given-names: Yufeng
    email: louiswang524@gmail.com
version: "0.3.0"
date-released: "2026-07-23"
abstract: >-
  FounderBench is a controlled benchmark for evaluating LLM agents on sequential
  startup-like decisions under bounded resources. Agents choose structured business
  actions in a deterministic simulator; task-specific scorers map final state to a
  0-100 outcome. Free-form rationale is logged but never scored.
repository-code: "https://github.com/louiswang524/FounderBench"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - llm
  - agents
  - benchmark
  - startup
  - sequential-decision-making
  - simulation
